nce, their potential for victimization. The book outlines the modern "inmate code" that governs prisoner behaviours, the formal controls put forth by the administration, the dynamics that shape sex-offender experiences of incarceration, and the personal growth experiences of many prisoners as they cope with incarceration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMale prisonersxInterviewsxCanada. 0aMale prisonersxPsychologyxCanada. 0aMale prisonersxSocial conditionsxCanada. 0aMale prisonerszCanadavInterviews. 0aMale prisonerszCanadaxPsychology. 0aMale prisonerszCanadaxSocial conditions. 0aPrisonsxSociological aspectsxCanada. 0aPrisonszCanadaxSociological aspects. 4aLaw. 4aPolitical Science: Social Policy. 4aPolitical Science: Social Services. 4aSocial Science: Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112054840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771120548423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771120548/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles